regularly. She is interested in depot medroxyprogesterone acetate (DMPA) injections but has concerns after reading about potential side effects online.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Her body mass index is 22 kg/m2.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about depot medroxyprogesterone acetate is most accurate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Weight gain occurs in all users within the first year","It is effective in treating endometriosis-associated pain","It is contraindicated in women with a history of pelvic inflammatory disease","It causes permanent amenorrhoea in 30% of users","Bone mineral density loss is irreversible after five years of use"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDepot medroxyprogesterone acetate (DMPA) is a long-acting reversible contraceptive that works primarily by suppressing ovulation. Understanding its effects and side effects is crucial for appropriate counselling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is effective in treating endometriosis-associated pain\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. DMPA suppresses ovulation and induces endometrial atrophy, which effectively reduces endometriosis-associated pain. The continuous progestogenic effect leads to decidualisation and eventual atrophy of endometrial tissue, including ectopic endometrial tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt is contraindicated in women with a history of pelvic inflammatory disease\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. DMPA is not contraindicated in women with previous pelvic inflammatory disease. In fact, it may provide some protection against future pelvic inflammatory disease by thickening cervical mucus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeight gain occurs in all users within the first year\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While weight gain is a common side effect, it does not affect all users. Studies show an average weight gain of 2-3 kg in the first year, with approximately 25% of users gaining more than 5 kg.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBone mineral density loss is irreversible after five years of use\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While DMPA use is associated with decreased bone mineral density, this effect is largely reversible after discontinuation, even with long-term use. Most women recover their bone mineral density within 2-3 years of discontinuation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt causes permanent amenorrhoea in 30% of users\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. While DMPA commonly causes amenorrhoea, fertility and regular menstrual cycles typically return within 6-18 months after the last injection. The median time to conception is 10 months after the last injection.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Depot medroxyprogesterone acetate (DMPA) causes reversible bone mineral density loss which recovers after discontinuation.","DMPA is an effective treatment for endometriosis-associated pain through ovulation suppression.","Weight gain is a common side effect of DMPA, with average gains of 2-3 kg in the first year."],"references":["Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (RANZCOG). Contraception [Internet]. Melbourne: RANZCOG; 2023 [cited 2024 Jun 23]. Available from: https://ranzcog.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/Contraception-Clinical-Guideline.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53475"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16966"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53475","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53475"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-08T13:14:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-08T13:16:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9656"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"68010"}}